  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2021-02-24",
    "date": "2021-04-07T19:58:33Z",
    "text": "Vote by Mail Tracking Act\n\nThis bill requires mail-in ballots to (1) contain a U.S. Postal Service (USPS) barcode that enables tracking of each individual ballot, (2) satisfy USPS requirements for ballot envelope design and machinable letters, and (3) include the official election mail logo.\n\nThe federal government must reimburse each state (including the District of Columbia and any U.S. territory or possession) for the cost of using the barcode service."
  },
